close_reason: "Implemented in feat/gc-storage-durability: pending-refresh queue + gate added to embeddings GC targets; tests + docs updated; 100% coverage."
body: "## Context\n\n`src/cli/commands/gc.ts:22-48` defines GC_TARGETS. The embeddings scope covers:\n- `search/embeddings.jsonl`\n- `search/vectorization-status.json`\n- `search/lancedb/`\n\nBut NOT `search/pending-refresh.json` (written by `src/core/search/background-refresh.ts:136`).\n\nAfter gc --scope embeddings, if a background worker is still running or a queued file exists, the worker drains the queue, calls refreshSemanticEmbeddingsForMutatedItems, reads the (now empty) ledger as '{}', and upserts only the queued items into a fresh vector store — leaving the remaining 1056 items unindexed with no warning.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n\n- [ ] Add `search/pending-refresh.json` to the embeddings GC_TARGETS\n- [ ] OR: when gc --scope embeddings runs, acquire the reindex lock briefly to flush and discard the pending queue\n- [ ] Document that gc --scope embeddings invalidates the entire semantic index (requires pm reindex --mode semantic to rebuild)\n- [ ] Add a test that verifies the pending queue is cleared after gc\n\n## Evidence\n\n- `src/cli/commands/gc.ts:29-47` — embeddings targets list; pending-refresh.json absent\n- `src/core/search/background-refresh.ts:61-66` — pending queue path = `search/pending-refresh.json`\n- `.agents/pm/search/pending-refresh.json` present in this repo (currently contains 11 bytes)"
